text.tspan: Number of tests per confirmed case vs. Estimated percentage of
symptomatic COVID-19 cases reported (Russel et al.)
Data relates to the 7-8 April. The diagonal line marks the line of best fit.
Data for Russia has been excluded here as an outlier.
Estimated percentage of symptomatic COVID-19 cases reported
Source: Test per case is based on official data collated by Our World in Data and European CDC – Situation Update Worldwide. Estimates of the
rate of case reporting are from Russell et al.
Note: For testing figures, there are substantial differences across countries in terms of the units, whether or not all labs are included, the extent
to which negative and pending tests are included and other aspects. Details for each country can be found at the linked page.
